{
  "texts": [
    "For an empirical comparison of the two strategies on our data, see Appendix D. 1.",
    "In full answer generation (FA), we let the LLM produce a full answer for each respondent in the survey sample, and then aggregate the answers by subpopulation in order to estimate their probability distributions.",
    "With this strategy, LLM answers may need post-processing, as they may not exactly correspond to one of expected answers (e.g.",
    "Pretty happy\" instead of \"B.",
    "Quite happy\")."
  ]
}